<br>
I didn't look at it, but you shouldn't be so worried about trying to fit into some sort of style set. Develop your own style.<br>
<br>
Also, you need to learn to compress images. BMP's are uncompressed images, and therefore, VERY large in file size. If you made it into a JPG or GIF, it would be much smaller. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shiro@polykarbonbbs>Shiro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/7/03 5:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2280.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Yes, but..</span><hr size=1> Actually I know how to convert them, this picture is actually not convertet because the coloring was made by someone else who didnt do this.<br>
